item.original:
Welcome to the Activity Wizard!
The Activity Wizard is an assessment tool that allows you to create detailed networking scenarios for other users. The typical sequence in making an activity is as follows:
1) Create the answer network and set the assessment items. 2) Create the initial network, which will be the user's starting point. A blank initial network may also be used. For accurate scoring, device display names in the initial network must match the ones in the answer network. 3) Put constraints on the user's ability to use certain features during the activity. 4) Write a clear set of instructions for the activity. 5) Password-protect the activity to prevent unauthorized changes to activity parameters. 6) Save the activity.
Please refer to the Activity Wizard help files for more detailed information.

请参考活动向导帮助文件的更详细的信息。

item.original:
The Variable Manager provides the ability for an activity author to add dynamic capabilities into an activity. These capabilities allow an author to create activities that change each time they are loaded or reset. This capability is enabled by creating pools of values and then creating variables which use the pool values to enable dynamic capabilities. The variables allow you to change many aspects of an activity, including but not limited to, Device names, IP addressing, Routing statements, DHCP and DNS records.
Quick Reference: for a full guide, see the Packet Tracer help files. There are four types of variables that can be created in the Variable Manager. They are identified by the tabs at the top of this page. With the exception of the Seeds, the variables are created using a combination of a resource pool and an associated variable. Each type tab has a place to enter both the pool and the variable information. The seeds tab, due to the simplicity of the type combine both parts into one operation.
How to create a variable: 1. Fill in the variable Name 2. Select the associated Pool Name (the pool must be already created to show in the dropdown list) 3. Specify the Variable Type (dropdown: Random, Element Position, Seed, Entire Range) 4. Specify the Value (if Element Position is selected a number within the range of values is specified, if seed is selected a seed name is entered for the value)
Variables can select values in one of 4 ways. Random C Any value in the pool. Element Position C An integer value that selects the same position from the pool each time. Seed C A position defined by a Seed variable in the Seed tab. A method for allowing the same position to be used in multiple variable selections. Entire Range C A variable used in the Activity Wizard answer network to accept any input as correct as long as it is contained in the associated pool.
item.text:
变量管理器提供了一个活动的能力作者将动态能力添加到一个活动。这些功能允许作者创建的活动改变每次加载或重置。启用此功能通过创建的值然后创建变量池使用池值启用动态能力。变量允许您更改一个活动的许多方面,包括但不限于,设备名称、IP寻址、路由语句,DHCP和DNS记录。
快速参考：对于一个完整的指南,请参阅Packet Tracer帮助文件。有四种类型的变量,可以在创建变量管理器。他们发现这个页面的顶部。除了种子,变量是使用的组合创建一个资源池和一个相关的变量。每种类型选项卡中有一个地方输入池和变量信息。种子选项卡,由于简单的类型两个部分合并成一个操作。
如何创建一个变量： 1. 填写变量名 2. 选择相关的池名称(池必须已经创建下拉列表中显示) 3.指定变量类型(下拉：随机的,元素的位置,种子,整个范围) 4. 选择指定的值(如果元素的位置指定值的范围内,如果选择种子种子名称输入值)
变量可以选择值的四种方法之一。 池中随机 -- 任何值。 元素的位置 -- 一个整数值,每次从池中选择相同的位置。 种子,种子的种子变量定义的位置选项卡。一个方法允许相同的位置中使用多个变量的选择。 整个范围,活动中使用一个变量向导回答网络接受任何输入正确只要是包含在相关的池。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] features a single Ethernet port that can connect a LAN backbone which can also support either six PRI connections to aggregate ISDN lines, or 24 synchronous/asynchronous ports.

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] features four Ethernet ports for multifunction solutions that require higher-density Ethernet than the mixed-media network modules.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]特性四个以太网端口多功能解决方案,需要高密度比混合介质以太网网络模块。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] provides a single Ethernet port with two WIC slots that can support a single Ethernet LAN, together with two serial/ISDN backhaul lines, and still allow multiple serial or ISDN in the same chassis.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]提供了一个单一的以太网端口和两个WIC插槽可以支持一个以太局域网,连同两个串行/ ISDN回程线,而且还允许多个串行或ISDN在同一底盘。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] Module provides one Fast-Ethernet interface for use with fiber media. Ideal for a wide range of LAN applications, the Fast Ethernet network modules support many internetworking features and standards. Single port network modules offer autosensing 10/100BaseTX or 100BaseFX Ethernet.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]模块提供一个以太网络接口与纤维媒体使用。适合广泛的局域网应用,快速以太网网络模块支持许多网络互连功能和标准。单独的端口网络模块提供autosensing 10/100BaseTX或100 basefx以太网。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] Module provides one Fast-Ethernet interface for use with copper media. Ideal for a wide range of LAN applications, the Fast Ethernet network modules support many internetworking features and standards. Single port network modules offer autosensing 10/100BaseTX or 100BaseFX Ethernet. The TX (copper) version supports virtual LAN (VLAN) deployment.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]模块提供一个以太网络接口使用铜的媒体。适合广泛的局域网应用,快速以太网网络模块支持许多网络互连功能和标准。单独的端口网络模块提供autosensing 10/100BaseTX或100 basefx以太网。TX(铜)版本支持虚拟LAN(VLAN)部署。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] Module provides one Fast-Ethernet interface for use with copper media, in addition to two Wan Interface Card expansion slots. Ideal for a wide range of LAN applications, the Fast Ethernet network modules support many internetworking features and standards. Single port network modules offer autosensing 10/100BaseTX or 100BaseFX Ethernet. The TX (copper) version supports virtual LAN (VLAN) deployment.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]模块提供一个以太网络接口使用铜的媒体,除了两个广域网接口卡扩展槽。适合广泛的局域网应用,快速以太网网络模块支持许多网络互连功能和标准。单独的端口网络模块提供autosensing 10/100BaseTX或100 basefx以太网。TX(铜)版本支持虚拟LAN(VLAN)部署。

item.original: The single-port Cisco Gigabit Ethernet Network Module (part number [[MODULE_NAME]]) provides Gigabit Ethernet copper connectivity for access routers. The module is supported by the Cisco 2691, Cisco 3660, Cisco 3725, and Cisco 3745 series routers. This network module has one gigabit interface converter (GBIC) slot to carry any standard copper or optical Cisco GBIC.
item.text: 广泛Cisco千兆以太网模块(部件编号[[MODULE_NAME]])提供千兆以太网铜连接路由器的访问。该模块支持Cisco2691年,Cisco3660年,Cisco3725年,Cisco3745系列路由器。这个模块有一个千兆网络接口转换器(GBIC)槽携带任何标准铜或光学CiscoGBIC。

item.original: The single-port Cisco Gigabit Ethernet Network Module (part number [[MODULE_NAME]]) provides Gigabit Ethernet optical connectivity for access routers. The module is supported by the Cisco 2691, Cisco 3660, Cisco 3725, and Cisco 3745 series routers. This network module has one gigabit interface converter (GBIC) slot to carry any standard copper or optical Cisco GBIC.
item.text: 广泛Cisco千兆以太网模块(部件编号[[MODULE_NAME]])提供千兆以太网光纤连接路由器的访问。该模块支持Cisco2691年,Cisco3660年,Cisco3725年,Cisco3745系列路由器。这个模块有一个千兆网络接口转换器(GBIC)槽携带任何标准铜或光学CiscoGBIC。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] provides two Ethernet ports with two WIC slots that can support two Ethernet LANs, together with two serial/ISDN backhaul lines, and still allow multiple serial or ISDN in the same chassis.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]提供了两个以太网端口和两个WIC插槽可以支持两个以太局域网,连同两个串行/ ISDN回程线,而且还允许多个串行或ISDN在同一底盘。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] Module provides two Fast-Ethernet interfaces for use with copper media, in addition to two Wan Interface Card expansion slots. Ideal for a wide range of LAN applications, the Fast Ethernet network modules support many internetworking features and standards.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]模块提供两个以太网络接口使用铜的媒体,除了两个广域网接口卡扩展槽。适合广泛的局域网应用,快速以太网网络模块支持许多网络互连功能和标准。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] Module provides two WAN Interface Card expansion slots. It can be used with a broad range of interface cards, supporting a diverse array of physical media and network protocols.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]模块提供两个广域网接口卡扩展槽。它可以用于广泛的接口卡,支持多样的物理媒体和网络协议。

item.original: The 4-port asynchronous/synchronous serial network module provides flexible multi-protocol support, with each port individually configurable in synchronous or asynchronous mode, offering mixed-media dial support in a single chassis. Applications for Asynchronous/Synchronous support include: Low speed WAN aggregation (up to 128 Kbps), dial-up modem support, Async or Sync connections to management ports of other equipment, and transport of legacy protocols such as Bi-sync and SDLC.
item.text: 并异步/同步串行网络模块提供了灵活的多协议支持,单独与每个端口可配置在同步或异步模式下,提供混合介质拨号支持在一个底盘。对异步/同步支持应用程序包括：低速WAN聚合(高达128 Kbps),拨号调制解调器的支持,异步或同步连接其他设备的管理端口,和运输遗留协议Bi-sync和SDLC等。

item.original: The 8-port asynchronous/synchronous serial network module provides flexible multi-protocol support, with each port individually configurable in synchronous or asynchronous mode, offering mixed-media dial support in a single chassis. Applications for Asynchronous/Synchronous support include: Low speed WAN aggregation (up to 128 Kbps), dial-up modem support, Async or Sync connections to management ports of other equipment, and transport of legacy protocols such as Bi-sync and SDLC.
item.text: 8-port异步/同步串行网络模块提供了灵活的多协议支持,单独与每个端口可配置在同步或异步模式下,提供混合介质拨号支持在一个底盘。对异步/同步支持应用程序包括：低速WAN聚合(高达128 Kbps),拨号调制解调器的支持,异步或同步连接其他设备的管理端口,和运输遗留协议Bi-sync和SDLC等。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] Integrated V.92 analog modem network module provides cost-effective analog telephone service connectivity for lower-density remote-access service (RAS), dial-out and fax-out modem access, asynchronous dial-on-demand routing (DDR) plus dial backup, and remote router management. Both the 8-port and 16-port versions use RJ-11 jacks to connect the integrated modems to basic analog telephone lines on the public switched telephone network (PSTN) or private telephony systems.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]综合V.92模拟调制解调器网络模块提供具有成本效益的模拟电话服务连接性与远程访问服务(RAS),同一和fax-out调制解调器访问、异步dial-on-demand路由(DDR)+拨号备份和远程路由器的管理。8-port和16-port版本使用RJ-11插孔连接集成调制解调器的基本模拟电话线路的公共交换电话网络(PSTN)或私人电话系统。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] card features dual RJ-11 connectors, which are used for basic telephone service connections. The WIC-1AM uses one port for connection to a standard telephone line, and the other port can be connected to a basic analog telephone for use when the modem is idle.
item.text: [[MODULE_NAME]]卡功能双重RJ-11连接器,用于基本电话服务连接。WIC-1AM使用一个端口连接到一个标准的电话线,和其他端口可以连接到一个基本的模拟电话调制解调器空闲时使用。

item.original: The [[MODULE_NAME]] is a single-port 10 Mbps Ethernet interface card, for use with 10BASE-T Ethernet LANs.

item.original: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. item.original: The type of route. Note that the values direct(3) and indirect(4) refer to the notion of direct and indirect routing in the IP architecture. Letting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipRouteTable object. That is, it effectively disassociates the destination identified with said entry from the route identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ip RouteType object.

item.original: A textual description of the entity. This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software.
item.text: 的文本描述的实体。这个值应该包括完整的名称和版本识别系统的硬件类型,软件操作系统和网络软件。

item.original: The vendor's authoritative identification of the network management subsystem contained in the entity. This value is allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree (1.3.6.1.4.1) and provides an easy and unambiguous means for determining `what kind of box' is being managed. For example, if vendor `Flintstones, Inc.' was assigned the subtree 1.3.6.1.4.1.424242, it could assign the identifier 1.3.6.1.4.1.424242.1.1 to its `Fred Router.'
item.text: 供应商的权威鉴定中包含网络管理子系统的实体。这个值是分配在重度子树(1.3.6.1.4.1)和企业提供了一个简单而明确的方式确定什么样的盒子被管理。例如,如果供应商的场景,Inc .的子树1.3.6.1.4.1.424242被分配,它可以指定标识符1.3.6.1.4.1.424242.1.1弗雷德路由器。

item.original: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.
item.text: 时间(数秒)由于网络管理的系统部分最后被重新初始化。

item.original: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person. If no contact information is known, the value is the zero-length string.
item.text: 文本识别的联系人管理节点,连同如何联系这个人的信息。如果没有联系信息是已知的,价值是零长度字符串。

item.original: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name. If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.
item.text: 一个administratively-assigned名托管节点。按照惯例,这是节点的完全限定域名。如果名称是未知的,价值是零长度字符串。

item.original: The physical location of this node (e.g., 'telephone closet, 3rd floor'). If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.
item.text: 这个节点的物理位置(例如,电话里,三楼)。如果地址不详,值是零长度字符串。

item.original: The number of network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.
item.text: 网络接口的数量(无论其当前状态)出现在这个系统。

item.original: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber.
item.text: 界面的列表条目。条目的数量是由ifNumber的价值。

item.original: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.
item.text: 一个条目包含管理信息适用于一个特定的接口。

item.original: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.
item.text: 一个独特的价值,大于零,对于每一个接口。建议值从1开始连续分配。每个接口的值子层必须保持不变,至少从一个初始化实体的网络管理系统初始化。

item.original: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware/software.
item.text: 一个文本字符串包含的信息接口。这个字符串应包括制造商的名称,产品名称和版本的硬件/软件的接口。

item.original: The type of interface. Additional values for ifType are assigned by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (IANA), through updating the syntax of the IANAifType textual convention.
item.text: 接口的类型。ifType额外的值被分配由互联网地址分配机构(IANA),通过更新IANAifType文本的语法约定。

item.original: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.
item.text: 规模最大的包可以发送/接收接口,在八位字节指定。接口用于传输网络数据报,这是规模最大的网络数据报,可以发送接口。

item.original: The interface's address at its protocol sub-layer. For example, for an 802.x interface, this object normally contains a MAC address. The interface's media-specific MIB must define the bit and byte ordering and the format of the value of this object. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.
item.text: 在子层协议接口的地址。例如,对于一个802年。x接口,这个对象通常包含一个MAC地址。接口的媒体相关MIB必须定义的位和字节顺序和格式的值对象。等接口,没有一个地址(例如,一个串行线),这个对象应该包含一个八位字节串零长度。

item.original: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. When a managed system initializes, all interfaces start with ifAdminStatus in the down(2) state. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, ifAdminStatus is then changed to either the up(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the down(2) state).
item.text: 所需的接口。测试(3)状态表明没有操作包可以被传递。管理系统初始化时,所有接口开始的ifAdminStatus(2)状态。由于明确的管理行动或/管理系统配置信息保留,ifAdminStatus然后改变了(1)或测试(3)州(或仍在下降(2)状态)。

item.original: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. If ifAdminStatus is down(2) then ifOperStatus should be down(2). If ifAdminStatus is changed to up(1) then ifOperStatus should change to up(1) if the interface is ready to transmit and receive network traffic; it should change to dormant(5) if the interface is waiting for external actions (such as a serial line waiting for an incoming connection); it should remain in the down(2) state if and only if there is a fault that prevents it from going to the up(1) state; it should remain in the notPresent(6) state if the interface has missing (typically, hardware) components.
item.text: 当前操作状态的接口。测试(3)状态表明没有操作包可以被传递。如果ifAdminStatus(2)然后ifOperStatus应该(2)。如果ifAdminStatus改为(1)然后ifOperStatus应该改变(1)如果接口准备发送和接收网络流量;应该改变休眠(5)如果界面等待外部动作(如串行线等待传入连接);它应该保持在(2)状态当且仅当有故障,防止它去(1)状态;它应该留在notPresent(6)状态的接口是否有缺失(通常情况下,硬件)组件。

item.original: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.
item.text: 当时的价值sysUpTime进入当前操作状态的接口。如果当前状态是进入前最后一个初始化的本地网络管理子系统,那么这个对象包含一个零值。

item.original: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.
item.text: 八位字节的总数收到接口,包括框架字符。

item.original: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer.
item.text: 数据包的数量,由这个子层更高(子)层,这并没有解决多播或广播地址在这个子层。

item.original: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.
item.text: non-unicast的数量(即。subnetwork-broadcast或subnetwork-multicast)数据包送到一个更高级别的协议。

item.original: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.
item.text: 被选出的入站信息包的数量被丢弃,即使没有错误被检测到,防止他们被交付一个更高级别的协议。一个可能的理由抛弃这样一个包是免费的缓冲区空间。

item.original: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of inbound transmission units that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.
item.text: 为接口,所以它的入站信息包含有错误阻止他们被交付到一个更高级别的协议。面向字符或固定长度的接口,入站传输的数量单位,包含错误阻止他们交付到更高级别的协议。

item.original: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of packets received via the interface which was discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces that support protocol multiplexing the number of transmission units received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. For any interface that does not support protocol multiplexing, this counter will always be 0.
item.text: 所以它的接口,通过接口接收的数据包的数量被丢弃,因为一个未知的或不支持的协议。对于面向字符或固定长度的接口,支持协议多路复用传输单位收到的数量通过接口被丢弃,因为一个未知的或不支持的协议。对于任何接口不支持协议多路复用,这个计数器将永远是0。

item.original: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.
item.text: 八位字节的总数传输的接口,包括框架字符。

item.original: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.
item.text: 总数更高级别的协议请求被传送的数据包,并没有解决多播或广播地址在这个子层,包括那些被丢弃或不发送。

item.original: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non-unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.
item.text: 数据包的总数更高级别的协议要求传输non-unicast(即。,subnetwork-broadcast或subnetwork-multicast)地址,包括那些被丢弃或不发送。

item.original: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.
item.text: 出站数据包的数量,选择被丢弃,即使没有错误被检测到被传播。一个可能的理由抛弃这样一个包是免费的缓冲区空间。

item.original: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of outbound transmission units that could not be transmitted because of errors.
item.text: 所以它的接口,出站数据包的数量不可能因为错误传播。面向字符或固定长度的接口,对外传播的数量单位,不能因为错误传播。

item.original: The length of the output packet queue (in packets).
item.text: 输出数据包队列的长度(数据包)。

item.text: 国家结核控制规划服务器发出一个国家结核控制规划的回应。

item.original: The device's clock is not synced. Packet is dropped.
item.text: 设备的时钟不同步。就将数据包丢弃。

item.original: The packet must be manycast. Either NTP not synced or our stratum is above the manycaster. The packet is dropped.
item.text: 数据包必须manycast。国家结核控制规划不同步或我们的地层是manycaster上面。包被删除。

item.original: There is an indication of a non-fatal violation of protocol as the result of a programming error, long - delayed packet, or replayed packet.The peer process discards the packet and exits.
item.text: 非致命的信号有违反协议作为编程错误的结果,拖延已久的数据包,数据包或重播。对等过程中丢弃数据包并退出。

item.original: Authentication fails, send a crypto-NAK packet.

This indicates a fatal violation of protocol as the result of a programming error, long - delayed packet, or replayed packet.The peer process discards the packet, demobilizes the symmetric passive association, and exits.
item.text: 这表明一个致命的违反协议的编程错误,拖延已久的数据包,数据包或重播。对等过程中丢弃数据包,遣散对称被动协会,并退出。

item.original: This indicates a client (mode 3) unicast packet matching no association(mode 0). The server constructs a server(mode 4) packet and returns it to the client without retaining state.
item.text: 这表明客户端(模式3)单播数据包匹配(模式0)没有联系。服务器构造一个服务器(模式4)数据包,并将它返回给客户端没有保留状态。

item.original: The transmit timestamp is zero, the server is horribly broken. The packet is dropped.
item.text: 传输的时间戳是零,服务器严重破损。包被删除。

item.original: The transmit timestamp duplicates a previous one, the packet is a replay; therefore, dropped.
item.text: 传输时间戳重复前一个,包是一个回放;因此,下降。

item.original: It's a new manycast client ephemeral association. Authentication fails, the packet dropped.
item.text: 这是一个新的manycast客户短暂的协会。身份验证失败,包了。

item.original: It's a new manycast client ephemeral association. Authentication passes, the association is mobilized in the same version as in the packet.
item.text: 这是一个新的manycast客户短暂的协会。身份验证通过,协会动员在同一版本的包。

item.original: This is a unicast packet. The origin timestamp is zero(unsynchronized) or does not match the transmit timestamp(bogus). The packet is dropped.
item.text: 这是一个单播包。起源的时间戳是零(同步)或不匹配传输时间戳(假的)。包被删除。

item.original: The packet is a crypto-NAK; the server might have just changed keys. The packet is dropped.
item.text: 包是一个crypto-NAK;服务器可能只是换了钥匙。包被删除。

item.original: The association is authenticated; the key ID is nonzero and received packets fails authentication. The packet is dropped to avoid a bait - and-switch attack
item.text: 协会认证;key的ID是零和接收数据包认证失败。包被删除以避免诱饵 -- 并切换攻击

item.original: The packet indicates a new symmetric passive association. It is mobilized in the same version as in the packet. Authentication fails, send a crypto - NAK packet.
item.text: 包表明一个新的对称被动协会。动员在相同版本的包。身份验证失败,发送一个加密 -- 否定包。

item.original: If restrict no - mobilize, send a symmetric active packet instead
item.text: 如果限制没有动员,发送一个包而不是对称的活跃

item.original: New symmetric passive association.It is mobilized in the same version as in the packet.
item.text: 新的对称被动协会。动员在相同版本的包。

item.original: New broadcast client association. Authentication fails. The packet is dropped.
item.text: 新的播放客户端关联。身份验证失败。包被删除。

item.original: New broadcast client association. New broadcast is not enabled. The packet is dropped.
item.text: 新的播放客户端关联。新广播不启用。包被删除。

item.original: New broadcast client association. It is mobilized in the same version as in the packet.
item.text: 新的播放客户端关联。动员在相同版本的包。

item.original: The packet is valid. The packet is processed to compute offset, delay, and dispersion.
item.text: 包是有效的。数据包处理来计算偏移量,延迟、色散。

item.original: A route to a particular destination.
item.text: 一个路由到一个特定的目的地。

item.original: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to sch multiple entries is dependent on the table- access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.
item.text: 这条路线的目的地IP地址。一个条目的值0.0.0.0被认为是默认路由。多到一个目的地的路线可以出现在桌上,但同步信道多个条目定义的表 -- 访问机制依赖于使用的网络管理协议。

item.original: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.
item.text: 的索引值唯一地标识的本地接口应该达到这个路由的下一跳。接口被一个特定值的指数相同的接口ifIndex被相同的值。

item.original: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.
item.text: 这条路线的主要路由度量。这个指标的语义由路由协议中指定的路线的ipRouteProto价值。如果不使用这个指标,其值应该设置为1。

item.original: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface.)
item.text: 这个路由的下一跳的IP地址。(在路线的情况下一定会实现一个接口,它通过广播媒体,这个字段的值是代理的IP地址接口。)

item.original: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.
item.text: 通过这条路线是学到的路由机制。包含值网关路由协议并非意在暗示主人应该支持这些协议。

item.original: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct.
item.text: 最后一次更新这条路线以来的秒数或决心是正确的。

item.original: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the ipRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the ipRouteMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent ipRouteDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C If the value of the ipRouteDest is 0.0.0.0 (a default route), then the mask value is also 0.0.0.0. It should be noted that all IP routing subsystems implicitly use this mechanism.
item.text: 表明面具与目的地址之前logical-ANDed ipRouteDest字段中的值。对于那些不支持的系统任意子网掩码,一个代理结构的价值ipRouteMask通讯员ipRouteDest字段的值是否属于一个甲级,B或C网络,然后使用： 网络掩码 255.0.0.0甲级 255.255.0.0 b类 255.255.255.0 c类 如果ipRouteDest 0.0.0.0(默认路由),那么面具值也是0.0.0.0。应该注意的是,所有的IP路由子系统隐式地使用这种机制。

item.original: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route, as determined by the value specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.
item.text: 引用MIB定义特定于特定的路由协议负责这条路线,由指定的值在路线的ipRouteProto价值。如果此信息不存在,它的值应该设置为对象标识符{ 0 0 },这是一个语法有效的对象标识符,以及任何一致性实现asn . 1和误码率必须能够生成和识别这个值。

item.original: An entry containing IPv4-specific information for a specific interface.
item.text: 一个条目包含IPv4-specific信息为一个特定的接口。

item.original: The index value that uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IF-MIB's ifIndex.
item.text: 索引值唯一地标识该条目的接口都是适用的。接口被一个特定值的指数相同的接口相同的值作为确定的IF-MIB ifIndex。

item.original: The size of the largest IPv4 datagram that this entity can re-assemble from incoming IPv4 fragmented datagrams received on this interface.
item.text: 规模最大的IPv4数据报,这个实体可以重新组装,从传入的IPv4分散的数据报接收这个接口。

item.original: The indication of whether IPv4 is enabled (up) or disabled (down) on this interface. This object does not affect the state of the interface itself, only its connection to an IPv4 stack. The IF-MIB should be used to control the state of the interface.
item.text: 是否启用了IPv4的迹象()或禁用此接口(下降)。这个对象不影响接口本身的状态,只连接一个IPv4堆栈。IF-MIB应该用来控制接口的状态。

item.original: The time between retransmissions of ARP requests to a neighbor when resolving the address or when probing the reachability of a neighbor.
item.text: 之间的时间重发的ARP请求邻居时解决地址或探测一个邻居的可达性。

item.original: An entry containing IPv6-specific information for a given interface.
item.text: 一个条目包含IPv6-specific信息对于一个给定的接口。

item.original: The size of the largest IPv6 datagram that this entity can re-assemble from incoming IPv6 fragmented datagrams received on this interface.
item.text: 规模最大的IPv6数据报,这个实体可以重新组装,从传入的IPv6分散的数据报接收这个接口。

item.original: The Interface Identifier for this interface. The Interface Identifier is combined with an address prefix to form an interface address. By default, the Interface Identifier is auto-configured according to the rules of the link type to which this interface is attached. A zero length identifier may be used where appropriate. One possible example is a loopback interface.
item.text: 这个接口的接口标识符。接口标识符与一个地址前缀相结合形成一个接口地址。默认情况下,接口标识符自动配置根据这个接口的链接类型的规则。一个零长度的标识符可以在适当的地方使用。一个可能的例子是一个环回接口。

item.original: The time a neighbor is considered reachable after receiving a reachability confirmation.
item.text: 邻居后被认为是可以接受一个可达性确认。

item.original: The time between retransmissions of Neighbor Solicitation messages to a neighbor when resolving the address or when probing the reachability of a neighbor.
item.text: 之间的时间重发的邻居请求消息时,一个邻居解决地址或当探测一个邻居的可达性。

item.original: The IP Address that the peer is using as its source address. Note that on an unnumbered link, this may not be a member of any subnet on the system.
item.text: 同行使用的IP地址作为它的源地址。注意,在一个未编号的链接,这可能不是系统上的任何子网的一员。

item.text: EIGRP路由表及其相关属性为一个自治系统()中配置VPN拓扑表中。拓扑表中所有路由条目将由IP网络索引类型,IP网络数量和网络掩码(前缀)的大小。

item.text: 进入一个EIGRP在给定的拓扑表。

item.text: 值为true(1)表明路由到目标网络失败,一个活跃的(查询)寻找一个替代路径是在进步。值为假(2)指示的路线是稳定的(被动)。

item.original: A successor is the next routing hop for a path to the destination IP network number for a single route in the topology table in the AS. There can be several potential successors if there are multiple paths to the destination. This is the total number of successors for a topology entry.
item.text: 的继任者是下一个目的地IP网络路由跳路径数量的单一路线在拓扑表中。可以有多个潜在继任者如果有多个路径到目的地。这是一个拓扑继任者的总数。

item.original: The format of the IP address defined as the origin of this topology route entry.
item.text: IP地址的格式定义为这个拓扑路由条目的起源。

item.original: This is the next hop IP address for the route represented by the topology entry. The next hop is where network traffic will be routed to in order to reach the destination network for this topology entry. The format is governed by cEigrpNextHopAddressType.
item.text: 这是下一个跳IP地址的路由拓扑所代表的条目。下一跳就是网络流量将被路由到为了达到目的地网络拓扑条目。是由cEigrpNextHopAddressType格式。

item.text: 的接口到达下一跳的IP地址将网络流量发送到目的地所代表的网络拓扑。

item.original: The table of established EIGRP peers (neighbors) in the selected autonomous system. Peers are indexed by their unique internal handle id, as well as the AS number and VPN id. The peer entry is removed from the table if the peer is declared down.
item.text: 表建立了EIGRP的同行(邻居)选定的自治系统。同行是由其独特的内部处理索引id,以及数量和VPN id。同行的条目就会从表中删除如果同行宣布。

item.text: 一个对等的统计数据和操作参数。

item.text: 身份验证类型指定为一个区域。额外的身份验证类型可以转让本地在单位面积的基础上。

item.text: 广告链接的类型状态。每个链接状态类型都有一个单独的广告格式。

item.original: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.
item.text: 链接状态ID是一个LS型特定字段包含一个路由器ID或IP地址;它标识的路由域被广告所描述的。

item.original: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.
item.text: 签署的序列号字段是一个32位整数。它是用来检测旧广告和复制链接状态。序列号是线性的空间。序列号越大越最近的广告。

item.original: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.
item.text: 这个领域是链路状态的时代广告在几秒钟内。

item.original: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.
item.text: 这个领域的校验和完整的广告内容,除了年龄字段。年龄字段除外,这样可以增加广告的年龄没有更新校验和。使用的校验和是相同的用于ISO无连接数据报;它通常被称为弗莱彻校验和。

item.text: 边界网关协议更新信息包含路线撤离。

item.text: 边界网关协议更新信息包含更新的路线。

item.text: 边界网关协议更新信息包含新航线。

item.text: FTP客户端发送命令到FTP服务器类型。默认设置为二进制类型

item.text: FTP客户端发送被动命令到FTP服务器。

item.text: FTP客户端发送命令到FTP服务器的检索文件。

item.text: 存储文件的FTP客户端发送命令到FTP服务器。

item.text: 慢性消耗病的FTP客户端发送命令来改变当前工作目录FTP服务器。

item.text: FTP客户端发送pwd命令到FTP服务器知道当前的工作目录。

item.text: FTP客户端接收到一个受欢迎的消息从FTP服务器。

item.text: FTP客户端接收到响应的用户名。用户名是有效的。

item.text: FTP客户端接收到响应的密码。密码是有效的。

item.original: The FTP client receives the response for passive command from the FTP server. The server listens on passive port, waiting for the client to connect and start data transfer.
item.text: 被动FTP客户端接收到响应命令从FTP服务器。被动服务器监听端口,等待客户端连接并开始数据传输。

item.original: The FTP client receives the response for RETR command confirming that it is ready to send the file.
item.text: RETR FTP客户端接收到响应命令确认它已经准备好发送该文件。

item.original: The FTP client receives the response for LIST command confirming that it is ready to send the directory listing.
item.text: FTP客户端接收到响应列表命令确认它已经准备好发送目录清单。

item.original: The FTP client receives the response for QUIT command confirming that the server is willing to logout the current FTP session.
item.text: FTP客户端接收到响应退出命令确认服务器愿意注销当前的FTP会话。

item.text: FTP客户端接收到响应RNTO命令确认FTP服务器成功地重命名文件。

item.original: The FTP client receives the response for DELE command confirming that the FTP server has successfully deleted the file.
item.text: FTP客户端接收到响应删除命令确认FTP服务器已成功删除该文件。

item.original: The FTP client receives the response from the FTP server indicating that the user does not have permission or the file does not exist in the server.
item.text: FTP客户端接收到FTP服务器的响应,指示用户没有权限或文件不存在服务器。

item.original: The FTP client receives the response from FTP server indicating that the client failed in establishing a FTP data connection
item.text: FTP客户端接收到FTP服务器的反应表明客户端建立FTP数据连接失败

item.original: The FTP client receives the response from FTP server that user account does not exist.
item.text: FTP客户端接收到响应从FTP服务器,用户帐户不存在。

item.original: The FTP client receives response from the FTP server that the data transfer went successfully
item.text: FTP客户端收到响应从FTP服务器的数据传输成功

item.original: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IPv4 Router in respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IPv4 Routers forward datagrams. IPv4 hosts do not (except those source-routed via the host).
item.text: 表明该实体是否作为一个IPv4路由器在收到的数据包的转发,但不解决,这个实体。IPv4路由器转发数据报。IPv4主机不(除了那些source-routed通过主机)。

item.original: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IPv6 Router on any interface in respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IPv6 Routers forward datagrams. IPv6 hosts do not (except those source-routed via the host).
item.text: 的指示该实体是否充当IPv6路由器在尊重任何接口收到的数据包的转发,但不解决,这个实体。IPv6路由器转发数据报。IPv6主机不(除了那些source-routed通过主机)。

item.original: The table containing information used to construct Router advertisements.
item.text: 包含信息的表用于构造路由器广告。

item.original: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IPv6 Router on this interface with respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IPv6 Routers forward datagrams. IPv6 hosts do not (except those source-routed via the host).
item.text: 表明该实体是否充当IPv6路由器在这个界面对收到的数据包的转发,但不解决,这个实体。IPv6路由器转发数据报。IPv6主机不(除了那些source-routed通过主机)。

item.original: An entry containing information used to construct Router advertisements.
item.text: 一个条目包含用于构造路由器广告信息。

item.original: A flag indicating whether the router sends periodic Router advertisements and responds to router solicitations on this interface.
item.text: 标志指示是否路由器发送周期路由器广告和响应路由器请求接口。

item.original: The maximum time allowed between sending unsolicited Router advertisements from this interface
item.text: 发送不请自来的路由器之间的最长时间允许广告从这个接口

item.original: The minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited Router advertisements from this interface. The default is 0.33 * ipv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval, however, in the case of a low value for ipv6RouterAdver-tMaxInterval, the minimum value for this object is restricted to 3.
item.text: 路由器之间的最短时间允许发送不请自来的广告从这个接口。然而,默认是0.33 * ipv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval ipv6RouterAdver-tMaxInterval低价值的情况下,这个对象的最小值限制为3。

item.original: The true/false value to be placed into the 'managed address configuration' flag field in Router advertisements sent from this interface.
item.text: 真/假值放置到管理地址配置的国旗在路由器广告从这个接口。

item.original: The true/false value to be placed into the 'other stateful configuration' flag field in Router advertisements sent from this interface.
item.text: 真/假值放置到其他状态配置的国旗在路由器广告从这个接口。

item.original: The value to be placed in MTU options sent by the Router on this interface. A value of zero indicates that no MTU options are sent.
item.text: 要放在MTU选项的值由路由器发送在这个界面。值0表示没有发送MTU选项。

item.original: The value to be placed in the reachable time field in Router advertisement messages sent from this interface. A value of zero in the router advertisement indicates that the advertisement isn't specifying a value for reachable time.
item.text: 要放置在可获得的时间字段的值在路由器从这个接口发送广告信息。一个值为零的路由器广告表明,广告不指定一个值可到达的时间。

item.original: The value to be placed in the retransmit timer field in Router advertisements sent from this interface. A value of zero in the router advertisement indicates that the advertisement isn't specifying a value for retrans time.
item.text: 重新发送计时器的值被放置在路由器广告从这个接口。一个值为零的路由器广告表明,广告不是retrans次指定一个值。

item.original: The default value to be placed in the current hop limit field in Router advertisements sent from this interface. The value should be set to the current diameter of the Internet. A value of zero in the router advertisement indicates that the advertisement isn't specifying a value for curHopLimit. The default should be set to the value specified in the IANA web pages (www.iana.org) at the time of implementation.
item.text: 默认值是放置在当前跳限制在路由器广告从这个接口。的值应该设置为当前互联网的直径。一个值为零的路由器广告表明,广告不是为curHopLimit指定一个值。默认应该设置为指定的值在IANA网页(www.iana.org)的实现。

item.original: The value to be placed in the router lifetime field of Router advertisements sent from this interface. This value MUST be either 0 or between ipv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval and 9000 seconds. A value of zero indicates that the Router is not to be used as a default Router. The default is 3 * ipv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval.
item.text: 进入路由器的一生中字段值的路由器广告从这个接口。这个值必须是0或ipv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval至9000秒。值0表示路由器不能用作默认的路由器。默认是3 * ipv6RouterAdvertMaxInterval。

item.original: The feasibility (best) distance is the minimum distance from this Router to the destination IP network in this topology entry. The feasibility distance is used in determining the best successor for a path to the destination network.
item.text: 可行性(最好的)距离是最小距离这个路由器的目的地IP网络拓扑条目。中使用的可行性距离是决定最好的继任者一个目的地路径网络。

item.original: If the origin of the topology route entry is external to this Router, then this object is the IP address of the Router from which it originated. The format is governed by object cEigrpRouteOriginAddrType.
item.text: 如果外部拓扑路由条目的起源这个路由器,然后这个对象从它起源的路由器的IP地址。cEigrpRouteOriginAddrType的格式是由对象。

item.original: The computed distance to the destination network entry from this Router.
item.text: 计算距离目的地从这个路由器网络入口。

item.original: The computed distance to the destination network in the topology entry reported to this Router by the originator of this route.
item.text: 计算距离目的地网络拓扑中入口报道这个路由器的发起者的路线。

item.original: The source IP address used by the peer to establish the EIGRP adjacency with this Router. The format is governed by object cEigrpPeerAddrType.
item.text: 使用的源IP地址同行建立EIGRP邻接路由器。cEigrpPeerAddrType的格式是由对象。

item.original: The ifIndex of the interface on this Router through which this peer can be reached.
item.text: 接口的ifIndex在这个路由器通过这可以达到对等。

item.original: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the Router in the Autonomous System. By convention, to ensure uniqueness, this should default to the value of one of the router's IP interface addresses.
item.text: 一个32位整数唯一识别路由器在自治系统。按照惯例,为确保唯一性,这应该默认的值的一个路由器接口的IP地址。

item.original: The administrative status of OSPF in the Router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPF Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces.
item.text: 行政地位的OSPF路由器。价值“启用”表示,OSPF进程是活跃在至少一个接口;“禁用”禁用所有接口。

item.original: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the Router's attached areas.
item.text: 的配置参数和累积统计信息描述路由器的连接区域。

item.original: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of one of the Router's attached areas.
item.text: 的配置参数和累积统计信息描述路由器的连接的地区之一。

item.original: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this area's link-state database. This sum excludes external (LS type 5) link-state advertisements. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a Router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.
item.text: 32位无符号和链路状态广告的LS校验和包含在这个区域的链路状态数据库。这个和排除外部(LS型5)链路状态的广告。之和可以用来确定是否有路由器的链路状态数据库的变化,并比较两个路由器的链路状态数据库。

item.original: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating Router in the Autonomous System.
item.text: 32位的数字,惟一地标识原始路由器在自治系统。

item.original: A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAddress) uniquely identifying the neighboring Router in the Autonomous System.

item.original:
The Scripting Interface allows users to create script modules for adding new functionalities to Packet Tracer. Unlike ExApps, script modules are developed directly in Packet Tracer with no external development environment needed. Each pka/pkt file has its own file script module. The file script module is stopped once the file is closed. PT script modules are running as long as Packet Tracer is running and can be started and stopped manually. Please refer to the Scripting Interface help files for more detailed information.
The typical sequence in creating a script module is as follows:
item.text:
脚本编程接口允许用户创建脚本模块添加新功能Packet Tracer。与ExApps、脚本模块开发中直接Packet Tracer与不需要外部发展环境。每个pka / pkt文件都有自己的文件脚本模块。停止文件脚本模块一旦文件关闭。PT脚本模块运行只要Packet Tracer运行,可以手动启动和停止。请参阅脚本编程接口帮助文件的更详细的信息。
典型的序列在创建一个脚本模块如下：

item.original: Select one of these templates to jump-start on a script module. Selecting a new template will remove all changes made to this script module.
item.text: 选择其中一个模板来启动脚本模块。选择一个新的模板将删除所有更改这个脚本模块。

item.original: Set this script module's general info such as name, description, author info, password, startup option, and security privileges.
item.text: 设置这个脚本模块的一般信息,如名称、描述、作者信息,密码,启动选项,和安全权限。

item.original: Add and edit script engine files with ECMAScript language (JavaScript). Script module logics should be coded in the script engine. The script engine is persistent as long as the script module is running.
item.text: 添加和编辑脚本引擎文件使用ECMAScript语言(JavaScript)。脚本模块逻辑应该编写脚本引擎。脚本引擎持续只要脚本模块运行。

item.original: Add and edit custom interface files with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and images. Custom interface files are rendered in each device's Custom Interface tab as well as any web view launched by the script module. Custom interface states, including JavaScript, are erased once the rendering web view is closed or changed to another custom interface file.
item.text: 添加和编辑自定义接口文件和HTML,CSS,JavaScript和图片。自定义接口文件呈现在每个设备的自定义界面选项卡以及任何web视图脚本模块发起的。自定义接口,包括JavaScript,抹去曾经呈现web视图是封闭或更改到另一个定制的接口文件。

item.original: Add and edit data files with xml, csv, or any plain text data. They can be treated as files or as a hash table. Data can also be dynamically added or removed in code during runtime, and they are saved with the Packet Tracer options file for persistence. Saving or exporting the script module also saves the data.
item.text: 添加和编辑数据文件和xml、csv或任何纯文本数据。他们可以被视为文件或作为一个哈希表。数据也可以在运行时动态添加或删除代码,并保存Packet Tracer选项文件的持久性。储蓄或导出脚本模块还保存数据。

item.original: Save this script module to file. If this is the file script module, this button is disabled. Saving the current pkt/pka file will save the file script module changes.
item.text: 保存这个脚本模块文件。如果这是文件脚本模块,这个按钮是禁用的。保存当前pkt / pka文件将保存文件脚本模块更改。

item.original: Export or save this script module as a pts file. Other users can then import the pts file as a PT script module. New script modules must be exported and added as PT script modules before starting.
item.text: 导出或保存这个脚本模块为分文件。其他用户可以导入分文件作为PT脚本模块。新的脚本模块之前必须导出和作为PT添加脚本模块开始。

item.original: Export the scripts and interfaces of this script module to a .ts translation file. The exported file can then be opened by Qt Linguist for translation.
item.text: 导出的脚本,这个脚本模块的接口.ts翻译文件。导出的文件可以打开,Qt翻译的语言学家。

item.original: Changes to the script module while running are not reflected immediately. Stop and start the script module to take effect.
item.text: 修改脚本模块运行时没有反映。停止和启动脚本模块生效。

item.original: Open debug window to examine log messages and check script engine states.
item.text: 打开调试窗口检查日志消息,检查脚本引擎的状态。

item.original: Signing the script module demonstrates the authenticity of its contents. It allows the user to automatically accept script modules signed with the same publisher certificate. Use a PKCS #12 (.p12) file to sign. See Help for instructions on how to generate a .p12 file.
item.text: 签名脚本模块演示了其内容的真实性。它允许用户自动接受脚本模块与相同的出版商签署证书。使用PKCS # 12(.p12)文件签署。查看帮助说明如何生成一个.p12文件。

item.original: Setting a password prevents unauthorized changes or viewing of this file's scripts and custom interfaces. When a user is running this file, the Scripting interface cannot be accessed unless the correct password is entered. If the file is an activity file, the password used to access the Scripting interface is the Activity Wizard password.
item.text: 设置一个密码可以防止未经授权的更改或查看这个文件的脚本和定制接口。当用户运行这个文件,脚本编程接口无法访问,除非输入正确的密码。如果文件是一个活动文件,密码用于访问脚本编程接口是活动向导密码。

item.original: How does this script module start? If this is the file script module, it will always be on opening of the file (On Startup).
item.text: 这个脚本模块是如何开始的?如果这是文件脚本模块时,它总是会在打开的文件(在启动时)。

item.original: Prevent this script module from being removed or stopped. This option is only for permanent script modules.
item.text: 防止这个脚本模块删除或停止。这个选项只有永久脚本模块。

item.text: 允许打开文件即使安全特权不是理所当然。这个选项只有文件脚本模块。
